    "causal_summary": "Phase 018 left the Public MCP configs and packet docs in a partially cleaned state. The runtime already defaults many feature flags to ON, but stale config notes, mismatched packet docs, and incomplete packet artifacts make it unclear which environment variables still matter. The user wants the five Public MCP configs aligned, no `MEMORY_DB_PATH` overrides, no redundant `SPECKIT_*` flags in those checked-in env blocks, consistent `_NOTE_7` guidance for the seven opt-out flags, and direct verification that the code defaults match the docs.",
